  "text": "C-terminal domains [CITATION_1] , are freely attached by a flexible proline-rich peptide linker (hinge). The length of the hinge is extremely variable 16 amino acid residues in collagenase to 65 amino acid residues in MMP-15. The specific function of the hinge is not fully understood (Fig. 2) .",
